LitCode 0.2.203 - Version numbering automation and cosmetic changes

* Source files are now included in source_code.tex and not litcode.web.
* Date and time of compilation of code is now included in the footer of the first page. 
* Version number is now kept in a separate file: version.txt. This version number can be printed by executing
  the program with --version or -v flag.
* Thin space added in the definition of coderef. This makes sure that the last letter of a reference is not
  touching the right angle >
* shebangs have been removed as they serve no purpose now.
* All files related to the source code are taken as input to source_code.tex. styling_file.web and plsty.web
  are weaved together to allow proper referencing.